###########
# DPGConv #
###########

The encoding process used by dpg4x is based on the dpgconv script by Anton
Romanov (theli). If you think dpg4x is just dpgconv + GUI, you would not be far
wrong.

http://theli.is-a-geek.org/blog/static/dpgconv


########################
# Exquisite icon theme #
########################

All the icons used by dpg4x, belong to the Exquisite icon theme. Included in
kde-look under GPL license.

Thank you to Mimin Ladha (original Xp_Mad icon set), Ghast (action icons),
Guppetto (KDE port) and Nick Bargnesi (build script).

http://kde-look.org/content/show.php?content=14788


###########
# Pexpect #
###########

DPG for X includes code from the pexpect library, by Noah Spurrier.

Pexpect is a pure Python module that makes Python a better tool for controlling
and automating other programs.

http://www.noah.org/wiki/Pexpect


####################
# Gbadev.org forum #
####################

In the gbadev.org forum, Jaja and juhees announced the encoding of the first DPG
video in Linux. A lot of code and ideas have been taken from here.

Other contributors are: tepples, brian33x51, LunarCrisis, oofrab, bugmenot!,
Firon, LS5, relaxed, steveox28, sinclair44, HyperHacker, jjlawren, mobad,
Sigma83, shadowofdarkness, Mr. Pickesworth, weux, maya, techforumz, ninjalj,
nornagon, Cartman!, D_S, NorQue and gspawn.

http://forum.gbadev.org/viewtopic.php?t=7897


########################
# Elotrolado.net forum #
########################

In the elotrolado.net forum, werewolf released DpgEncoder, the first graphical
application for encoding DPG video in Linux.

Other contributors are: B4HamuT, David-Kun, lemus, Toz, DNKROZ, aiToRCiKi,
ozrocpablo, kusanagi99, esnaque, rom_kurt, DKnight, Soed, Mariner_I, Ear3ndil,
xyrer and jackjack.

http://www.elotrolado.net/hilo_dpgencoder-para-linux-version-0-0_587415


###############################
# Additional Acknowledgements #
###############################

We reserve a special mention to all the code that dpg4x uses behind the scenes.
Without them, the dpg4x project would not be affordable with the current
available resources.

Mplayer & Mencoder - http://www.mplayerhq.hu
MPlayer is a movie player for Linux. MEncoder is a simple movie encoder,
designed to encode MPlayer-playable movies to other MPlayer-playable formats.

Python - http://www.python.org
Python is a remarkably powerful dynamic programming language that is used in a
wide variety of application domains.

wxWidgets - http://wxwidgets.org
wxWidgets is a library that gives its applications a truly native look and feel
because it uses the platform's native API rather than emulating the GUI.

Boa-Constructor - http://boa-constructor.sourceforge.net
Boa Constructor is a cross platform Python IDE and wxPython GUI Builder.

